1
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,880
That means Aew

2
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:37,400
was actually secretly in a relationship
with Weerachai.

3
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:41,240
So we're not suspects anymore, right?

4
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:44,720
PREVIOUS EPISODE

5
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:49,080
In that house,
there was one room I managed to open.

6
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:52,320
But before I could see what was inside,
I had to run out first.

7
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,680
I think it must be a secret room.

8
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:57,040
Move everything out first.

9
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,760
Burn whatever can be burned.

10
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,360
Where are we going to keep the rest?

11
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,560
Puna, where are you?

12
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:10,240
I'm at Teacher Mueangphrai's house today.

13
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:12,120
Alright then, I'll come over.

14
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:15,240
Did you hear where Mr. Sonrak is going?

15
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,360
I don't know.

16
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:19,800
If we want to know,
I think we should follow him.

17
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:23,120
I'll figure out how to deal with him.

18
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,720
How are you going to deal with him?

19
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,280
Puna.

20
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,160
Yes, Mr. Sonrak.

21
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,800
Do you mind if I come in?

22
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,360
-Please do.
-Oh my!

23
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,840
Whoa, that startled me.

24
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,000
Oh my God.

25
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:47,080
Look at that. Even though
they're at different labels,

26
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,520
they still manage
to secretly meet at her house.

27
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,760
Show some respect
when you talk about Mr. Sonrak.

28
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:57,280
And I think Puna isn't like that.

29
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:00,120
Don't be so naive, Miss Maria.

30
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,520
Meeting at a house like this,
what else would they be doing

31
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:03,720
other than hooking up?

32
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,360
<i>Hooking, hooking up…</i>

33
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:08,400
<i>Hooking, hooking up…</i>

34
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,160
That's enough!

35
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,080
I'll go check myself

36
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,120
and see what he's doing here.

37
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,680
No.

38
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,560
I'll go.

39
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:22,680
Even though I don't
usually meddle or snoop,

40
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:24,000
I'll try my best.

41
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:30,800
Huh? Hey. Wait a second.

42
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,000
Not locked. Perfect.

43
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,440
This is heavy.

44
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,600
My fingers!

45
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,360
Ouch!

46
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,760
Oh, poor me.

47
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,440
Hey, over there.

48
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:46,800
I came to pick you and Teacher up,
so we can cook and eat at my place.

49
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:52,480
By the way, is no one else home?

50
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,840
Teacher went out. He should be back soon.

51
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,000
Oh, I see.

52
00:06:57,040 --> 00:07:00,560
No problem. We'll just wait for him then.

53
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:03,000
Okay. Just a moment.

54
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,120
Yes.

55
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:09,720
Did you hear that, Sophie?

56
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:13,040
Loud and clear, Miss Maria.

57
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:16,680
Mr. Sonrak is going to take Puna out
to eat at his place.

58
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,360
What am I going to do?

59
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:19,800
I don't know either.

60
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:20,960
I've taken care of it.

61
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,040
What did you take care of?

62
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,120
Keep it down. He might hear you.

63
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,480
Hey!

64
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,640
Did you remove Mr. Sonrak's car battery?

65
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,800
Yeah.

66
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:30,280
Smart move.

67
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,480
Now his car won't start,

68
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:35,520
so he can't take Puna out
to eat at his place.

69
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,000
-Yes!
-Amazing!

70
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:46,640
Could I switch places and go have dinner
with him instead of Puna?

71
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,040
No, he'll just keep thinking about Puna.

72
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,120
We should just go eat somewhere else.

73
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:54,200
Oh, I'll leave this to you.
Book a restaurant.

74
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:56,040
Which one should we go to?

75
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:58,240
Wait, excuse me.

76
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:59,640
How much longer
are you going to keep talking?

77
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,720
-A while.
-Yeah.

78
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:03,160
-Can you make it quick?
-No.

79
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:05,320
Hey. But I'm tired. It's heavy.

80
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,640
Geez.

81
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,880
Which arm feels heavy?

82
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:09,440
The right one.

83
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:11,320
-If it's heavy, use the other arm.
-Yeah.

84
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:14,720
Let me try. It's light. Hey!

85
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,800
Are you crazy? It's heavy on both sides!

86
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,000
Just put it down.

87
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:19,360
Oh my.

88
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,040
-Here's some water.
-Thank you.

89
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,160
Puna.

90
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:33,200
I've changed my mind.
We don't need to go to my place to cook.

91
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,640
Since we're already here,

92
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,640
we can just eat here.

93
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:42,679
Is that okay?

94
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,039
Yes, that's okay.

95
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:47,440
When Teacher Mueangphrai comes back,
we can all eat together.

96
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,520
How about that?

97
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:51,000
That would be better, right?

98
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,400
Let's go prepare the food.

99
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,200
Let's go!

100
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:00,840
-Ah!
-Shh!

101
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:02,120
Hold it in.

102
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,080
Hold it!

103
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:08,600
How did this happen?
I was so close to stopping it.

104
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:11,760
Why did he suddenly change his mind
and decide to eat here with her?

105
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,800
I don't know.

106
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:16,560
Yeah.
There's an African proverb that says…

107
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,520
What does that mean?

108
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,040
It means you can't compete
in rowing and paddling,

109
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,400
but you can compete in fate and destiny.

110
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,320
You crazy, you're saying it wrong.

111
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,560
Have you ever been to Africa?

112
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,040
-No.
-Then don't argue.

113
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,200
But this is Thailand.
We use Thai proverbs.

114
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:35,200
Yeah.

115
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:37,360
You can compete in rowing and paddling,

116
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,440
but you can't compete in fate and destiny.

117
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:41,000
Why can't I compete?

118
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,320
I've been competing with her all along.

119
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,960
And today, I'm not giving up.

120
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:48,640
Oh?

121
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,280
Here she goes.

122
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,320
Miss Maria is in full-on mode now.

123
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,320
Step aside! Wait for me.

124
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,640
Hey, what about the battery?

125
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,640
Up to you.

126
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:58,600
Whoa.

127
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,240
Oh man, I'm exhausted.

128
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:10,440
Puna, is there anything you're missing?
I can order it through an app for you.

129
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,160
No, everything's all set.

130
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,720
Puna!

131
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,840
I missed you so much!

132
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:26,920
Mr. Sonrak is here too?

133
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:31,800
Oh my, what a coincidence.
What a small world, really fate at work.

134
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:34,280
I never expected
to see you here, Mr. Sonrak.

135
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:37,080
Usually,

136
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,760
I come to Puna's house quite often.

137
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,640
Because Puna and I

138
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,600
are close friends.

139
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:44,720
Oh.

140
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,840
I just found out we're that close.

141
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,000
Hey.

142
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:55,280
What are you doing now?

143
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:59,880
There are vegetables and eggs here,
so probably doing some laundry.

144
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,640
Puna!

145
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:09,520
Would you like me to help?

146
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,160
I really love cooking.

147
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:14,560
Yes, Miss Maria is really good at cooking.

148
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,560
It's delicious too.

149
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,280
That's right.

150
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:22,040
What should we make today?

151
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,560
There's some pork belly.

152
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:27,680
How about stir-fried pork
with oyster sauce?

153
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,080
Wow!

154
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:32,160
Puna, go wash the pork, okay?

155
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:35,600
Chop the vegetables,
and peel the garlic too.

156
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,160
Once everything's ready,
I'll do the stir-fry myself.

157
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,480
Oh, there are a lot of people here.

158
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:48,920
Excuse me, Teacher.
I wanted to have Puna's cooking today.

159
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,000
I'm afraid today isn't convenient.

160
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,120
Why isn't it convenient?

161
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:56,720
I was just about to show
my cooking skills, Teacher.

162
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:57,840
Exactly.

163
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,560
It's not often Miss Maria
honors your house like this.

164
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:02,440
You should be happy.

165
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,360
But I just came back from the doctor.

166
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,960
The doctor said
I've caught a new strain of COVID.

167
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:08,040
Oh!

168
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:11,560
One of my lungs
is also infected with tuberculosis.

169
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,240
I've been told
not to stay in crowded places.

170
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:18,760
You guys shouldn't stay close to me.

171
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:26,960
Everyone.

172
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:28,960
I have a singing lesson.

173
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,480
Right? Okay.

174
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:32,120
-I should get going now.
-Time to go.

175
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,040
-Let's go. It's time.
-See you.

176
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,720
Bye!

177
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:38,720
Then I'll head back first.
I'll come to eat next time.

178
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,280
Yes, okay.

179
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:51,880
Thank you, Teacher. You're the best.

180
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:54,840
That was so smooth.

181
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,360
What's going on?

182
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,680
Hey.

183
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,000
Where did the car battery go?

184
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,040
Maria!

185
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:44,960
Maria, come here.

186
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,800
You called me?

187
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:48,280
Yes, come here quickly.

188
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,760
What is it, Mr. Sonrak?

189
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:56,200
The thing is, my car

190
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:59,840
won't start. The battery is missing.

191
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:02,920
I didn't take it.

192
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,200
I didn't take it either.

193
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:05,560
I didn't do it.

194
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:07,240
-You didn't do it?
-Yes.

195
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:09,320
Then why are your hands so dirty?

196
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,000
-Oh.
-Huh?

197
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:17,080
My hands got dirty
from the soot from the kitchen pot.

198
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,400
With a face like yours,
you know what soot is?

199
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:22,000
Have you ever cooked over a wood fire?

200
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:24,640
Cooking over a wood fire
exists everywhere!

201
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:27,240
The soot from the kitchen pot.

202
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:29,080
So you're not going to admit you did it?

203
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,440
It really wasn't us.

204
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:34,040
If you didn't do it, you can go.

205
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,960
Thank you.

206
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,120
Let's go.

207
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,160
-Wait.
-Yes?

208
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:39,920
Go that way.

209
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:40,880
What?

210
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:43,280
We're going this way home. Why that way?

211
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,680
To push the car.

212
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:45,800
-What?
-Huh?

213
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:46,760
Hey.

214
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:49,160
We didn't steal the battery.
Why do we have to push the car?

215
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,120
Right.

216
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,240
There's no one else around here
except you guys,

217
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:53,760
so you're the ones who have to push it.

218
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:57,120
Mr. Sonrak, I really can't push it.

219
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,080
Can't push it?

220
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:01,000
I have a fragile model body.
I can't push it either.

221
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:01,960
Can't push it?

222
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:04,400
If you can't push it,
I'll fire all of you!

223
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,320
What?

224
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,440
Hey! Hurry up. Let's push it!

225
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,640
Yes.

226
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,240
Oh man, I'm doomed.
I shouldn't have taken the battery.

227
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,160
Stop complaining, or you'll get fired.

228
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,640
Go, push it!

229
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,480
-Ugh!
-So heavy.

230
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,080
Put some strength into it!

231
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,840
All right, let's do it!

232
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,600
Oh my.

233
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,400
Puna!

234
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:35,840
Yes, Teacher?

235
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:39,400
I know now which song you should sing.

236
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,600
Here.

237
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:44,800
SOFT HEART

238
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:45,880
BACK THEN, MY HEART WAS STRONG

239
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:46,840
AS TOUGH AS A BAR OF STEEL

240
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:47,840
SO MANY MEN CHASED AFTER ME

241
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:49,200
Teacher.

242
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:51,520
This song is…

243
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:55,280
"Soft Heart" lyrics.
It's the song you used to sing for me.

244
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:58,520
It's on your Uncle Tharin's cassette tape.

245
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,720
SOFT HEART

246
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:10,600
You have to sing this song, Puna.

247
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,200
WHY DOES IT BURN, UNABLE TO ESCAPE?

248
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:15,640
LIKE IRON SOFTENED BY FIRE

249
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:17,040
BEFORE THE HAMMER STRIKES

250
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,360
IT BENDS ON ITS OWN

251
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,840
How did you get this song?

252
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,240
This song was written by Aunt Wilai

253
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,640
for the man she loved.

254
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:32,760
Aunt Wilai?

255
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:46,600
I'll do my best
to sing this song perfectly, Teacher.

256
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,560
Then sing it for me.

257
00:16:56,800 --> 00:17:02,880
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

258
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:11,040
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

259
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:16,400
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

260
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:20,119
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

261
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:25,839
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

262
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:31,360
<i>But now, my heart is starting to weaken</i>

263
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:38,360
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

264
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:42,840
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

265
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:46,080
<i>Every time I see his face</i>

266
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:51,000
<i>My heart pounds</i>

267
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:56,640
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

268
00:17:56,720 --> 00:18:03,160
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

269
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:07,800
<i>Just one teasing smile from him</i>

270
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:10,400
<i>Before I knew it</i>

271
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:15,200
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

272
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:21,640
<i>Back then, my heart had never wavered</i>

273
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:28,480
<i>Why does it burn, unable to escape?</i>

274
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:31,960
<i>Like iron softened by fire</i>

275
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:35,520
<i>Before the hammer strikes</i>

276
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:41,400
<i>It bends on its own</i>

277
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,920
Sorry if I was being rude.

278
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:18,520
I didn't mean to eavesdrop on you singing.

279
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,360
What are you doing here?

280
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,800
I just happened to pass by.

281
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:30,240
I heard the song, so I came in to listen.

282
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:34,760
Is that a new song of yours?

283
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:40,320
It's an old song,
but I want to cover it in my own version.

284
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:43,280
I'm about to submit it
to Boss Nok for consideration.

285
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,120
Good luck.

286
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:51,480
Do your best. I'll be cheering for you.

287
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:02,960
Chaiya, I have something
I want to give you.

288
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:06,360
What is it?

289
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:18,120
This is Uncle Tharin's amulet.

290
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,240
He gave it to me to wear when I was a kid.

291
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:27,800
But I want you to wear it,
so you'll be safe.

292
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,120
You're worried about me?

293
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,400
Hey.

294
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,840
I'll take care of myself.

295
00:20:56,960 --> 00:21:01,240
I'll stay safe. I won't let you down.

296
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:15,400
Chaiya!

297
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:19,640
There you are, Chaiya.

298
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,320
Hey.

299
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,640
I've been looking all over for you.

300
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:26,000
Madam Paula, is something wrong?

301
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:29,000
I already paid you the rent.

302
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:32,160
What's that look for?
I'm not here to collect rent.

303
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,800
I just want to ask you

304
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:36,080
about the things you left with me.

305
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,040
Come on.

306
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:40,680
Head home and explain it to me.

307
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:44,160
I want my curiosity
and doubts cleared up right now.

308
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:45,760
-I'll get going now.
-Hurry up!

309
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,120
Yes.

310
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,040
This is heavy.

311
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,680
-Put it here!
-Here?

312
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,120
Just put it down!

313
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,520
My room's ceiling leaks,
so water's been seeping in.

314
00:22:18,040 --> 00:22:20,200
All these documents are really important.

315
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:24,120
So I wanted to rent
an extra room to store them safely.

316
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,360
You know, ma'am.

317
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:29,400
The other day, you saw
that someone tried to break into my room.

318
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:32,080
I'm worried it might happen again.

319
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:36,560
I thought I'd keep all the documents
in the room I rent from you.

320
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:40,520
Aw, that makes sense.

321
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:43,360
Alright, go ahead, Chaiya.

322
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:46,160
At first, I thought you just wanted
to rent another room

323
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,600
to live in yourself.

324
00:22:49,760 --> 00:22:53,120
Your rental room is really sturdy.

325
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:56,440
Of course. I'm a single woman
living alone,

326
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:57,960
so I have to be prepared.

327
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,440
But

328
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:03,040
if I had a handsome guy or two

329
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:07,280
with solid abs by my side,
I'd feel much safer.

330
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:09,760
You can raise the rent if you want,

331
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:11,920
but please let me pay
at the end of the month.

332
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:14,920
Chaiya, I'm really upset!

333
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,640
What kind of person do you think I am?
A total penny-pincher?

334
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:19,920
No need to worry about that!

335
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,320
Feel free to use the room.

336
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,880
Alright? We're close.

337
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:25,720
If we can help each other,
we should. Okay?

338
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,760
Yes.

339
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:31,000
But you two still need
to clear things up with me first.

340
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:35,320
Clear up what exactly?

341
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:38,560
Alright, Chaiya.

342
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:41,680
Hey, about you leaving your stuff with me,

343
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:43,400
the real reason is

344
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,360
you wanted to get close to me, right?

345
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,720
This is just a little trick, isn't it?

346
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,680
Ma'am. I didn't think like that.

347
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:50,600
Hey.

348
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:52,200
Didn't think like that, huh?

349
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:55,120
Just say it. If you like me, make a move.

350
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:58,280
Say it straight. No need to be shy.
I'm an adult, you know.

351
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:01,120
Well…

352
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:04,360
Stop hesitating! If you like me,
just go for it! Marry me!

353
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:07,200
Here, I don't mind if it's a bit smaller.

354
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,160
Hey!

355
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:13,360
Just kidding!

356
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:17,080
Wait! You're blushing, Chaiya?

357
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:18,680
Oh, seriously.

358
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,480
Hold on.

359
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:22,000
Are you actually serious about me?

360
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:23,560
You mean it, right?

361
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:26,640
I'm not talking to you anymore.
I'd better go.

362
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:29,560
You're so shy! Look at him blushing.

363
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:31,320
Manat.

364
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,960
You're grinning.

365
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,080
Tell me, are you serious about me too?

366
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:37,320
You sneaky little tiger.

367
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,720
I just remembered I left the laundry out.

368
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:40,640
Looks like it's about to rain.

369
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,760
I'd better bring it in.

370
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:44,880
Hey, you two!

371
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,120
If neither of you is taking her,
then I will!

372
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,040
Whoa, go back the way you came!

373
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,400
Where else am I supposed to go?

374
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:51,960
Wherever you are, just stay there!

375
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:54,160
Stay where I am.
I'll ask just one quick question.

376
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:56,080
-What?
-What is your relationship with Jintara?

377
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:57,840
-<i>Watermelon, watermelon</i>
-<i>Watermelon, watermelon</i>

378
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,000
You idiot!

379
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:01,320
These pants are so cool.

380
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:02,960
-Hey, Sergeant.
-Oh.

381
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:04,440
Everything's all set.

382
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:07,360
-You've got the room organized, right?
-Hey, who am I?

383
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:09,360
This is Au!

384
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,560
Don't worry, I've got this.

385
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,680
I've put on a full flashy setup for you.

386
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:13,600
Gotcha!

387
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,760
-A full flashy setup, huh?
-Yes.

388
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,960
-Let me see.
-Sure.

389
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:21,200
After you, honored guest.

390
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:37,880
Seriously, Au.

391
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:42,240
-He has to see it for himself.
-He's here.

392
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:45,880
Hey, what happened?

393
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:49,480
You were shocked when you saw the room,
weren't you, Chaiya?

394
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:52,480
From now on, if the Singha guys
ever raid our room again,

395
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:53,400
they won't be suspicious

396
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:55,040
why it's locked.

397
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:56,040
Yeah!

398
00:25:56,680 --> 00:26:00,000
For spicy stuff,
you've gotta give it to Manat.

399
00:26:00,520 --> 00:26:02,880
Wow. What a talent.

400
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:05,440
He's all about the spicy stuff.

401
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:08,520
As for sponsors, that's me.

402
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,960
And the god

403
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:11,800
-of mischief award
-Yes.

404
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:13,960
-goes to you, Sergeant. Applause!
-Yes.

405
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,920
Of course.
Are you complimenting me?

406
00:26:16,560 --> 00:26:18,640
-Good job.
-Good at mischief? Oh!

407
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:22,400
Awesome, as always. It's me, Au!

408
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:26,000
Hey, hold on.

409
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:28,240
Were we tricked
into being called mischievous?

410
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,960
-Hey, not me! Just you.
-Huh?

411
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,600
You're so mischievous.

412
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:37,280
Just me? The mischievous one?

413
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:41,240
Ugh.

414
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:48,000
Did you eat something bad again?

415
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:49,720
Why are you like this?

416
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,040
That herbal thing.

417
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:53,160
I wanted to try it to slim down a bit,

418
00:26:53,240 --> 00:26:56,760
but every time I take it,
I end up in the bathroom.

419
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:02,080
You're already skinny enough.
Still trying to lose more?

420
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:04,480
Here, have an electrolyte drink.

421
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:05,480
Really?

422
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:17,920
I've talked with the lawyer
about the song "Soft Heart".

423
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:21,640
Even though it was recorded 20 years ago,

424
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:25,800
no one ever officially transferred
the copyright.

425
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,440
After Onanong passed away,

426
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:31,600
the rights legally went to the heir.

427
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:35,560
And the only heir right now

428
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:36,720
is you, Mueangphrai.

429
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:41,560
Then if we re-record this song,
it shouldn't be a problem.

430
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:51,680
I'm so happy

431
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:55,240
that you'll be the one
to carry on my song, "Soft Heart".

432
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:58,120
And I'm thrilled

433
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:00,800
to see your success coming.

434
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:04,120
You're not far from your dream

435
00:28:04,960 --> 00:28:08,640
of becoming a singer.

436
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:12,080
You can do it, dear. Keep going.

437
00:28:15,040 --> 00:28:16,800
Thank you so much, Aunt Wilai.

438
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:23,760
Aunt Wilai, did you know, "Soft Heart"

439
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,720
is one I've been secretly singing
since I was little?

440
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:32,000
And I've always wanted to know

441
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:36,000
who originally sang this song.

442
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:41,840
Aunt Wilai.

443
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:48,760
No one ever knew about this song.

444
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:52,600
How did you even find out about it?

445
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:57,720
I heard it from a cassette tape
that Uncle Tharin kept in the cabinet.

446
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:02,640
He was very protective of it.
He wouldn't let anyone touch it.

447
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:06,440
Whenever I wanted to listen,
I could only listen when he wasn't there.

448
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:15,760
Twenty years ago, this song
was recorded by Darathong Music.

449
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:17,840
But Kamnan Pong canceled its release

450
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:21,680
because of a misunderstanding about you.
Why did Tharin have a copy of this song?

451
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:24,720
I sent it to him.

452
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:31,800
Then why did Uncle Tharin
forbid me from singing it?

453
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:34,600
The song is so beautiful.
I just don't understand.

454
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:42,200
Since we're at it,

455
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:46,480
it's time I tell you the truth.

456
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:50,280
Aunt Wilai, do you know his reason?

457
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:54,360
Yes, because "Soft Heart"

458
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:57,120
is a song full of memories.

459
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:04,880
I wrote it for the man
I loved most in my life.

460
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,120
Wilai.

461
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,680
It's alright.

462
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:14,360
At least now,

463
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:17,320
Puna will know the story behind the song,

464
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:22,520
where the inspiration came from.

465
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:34,880
From the very first time I saw him,
my heart feels shaken?

466
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,960
Waver is better.

467
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:45,880
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

468
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:47,720
Waver.

469
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:55,000
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

470
00:30:56,200 --> 00:31:00,160
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

471
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:04,040
On! I'm back!

472
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:06,640
On!

473
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,400
Are you there?

474
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:11,600
Hey!

475
00:31:13,840 --> 00:31:15,320
What are you doing?
I've been calling for a while.

476
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:18,920
I've just been reading
a little of this and that.

477
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,440
Here, today I brought

478
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:28,000
my favorite, five-spice braised eggs,
and your favorite, shrimp paste chili.

479
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:31,560
That looks so good!

480
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,920
I was just about to ask
if there was anything to eat.

481
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:37,600
Today we'll eat as much as we want!

482
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:41,920
Are you free tomorrow night?
Let's go see the <i>Mor Lam</i> show.

483
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:45,160
-Tomorrow night?
-Yes,

484
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:47,240
the temple nearby
is holding a gilding ceremony.

485
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:49,880
Maybe we'll even meet the band leader.

486
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:51,920
I can ask them for singing gigs.

487
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:54,720
You've been talking
about wanting to be a singer, right?

488
00:31:58,320 --> 00:31:59,240
Yes.

489
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:00,480
Let's go together.

490
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:01,680
Okay.

491
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:44,920
On.

492
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:47,040
On.

493
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:50,600
On.

494
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:56,200
On, where are you?

495
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:02,120
On!

496
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:12,040
DON'T LOOK FOR ME
SOMEDAY, WE'LL MEET AGAIN

497
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:17,560
<i>Don't look for me.</i>

498
00:34:18,080 --> 00:34:21,280
<i>Someday, we'll meet again.</i>

499
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:23,960
<i>Take care of yourself.</i>

500
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:25,840
<i>From On.</i>

501
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:28,760
Why did you leave me?

502
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:32,120
Did I do something wrong, On?

503
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,080
On!

504
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:38,040
On!

505
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:43,120
On!

506
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:48,440
What did I do wrong, On?

507
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:51,920
On!

508
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:54,920
On!

509
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:12,840
So that means, you and my father…

510
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,160
Yes.

511
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:20,360
We were together.

512
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:23,480
<i>We were together.</i>

513
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:25,240
It was

514
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:30,000
before I ran away from Phupha
to become a singer in Bangkok.

515
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,560
But I swear,

516
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:40,920
even though we were once in love,

517
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:46,800
after Phupha married Namthip,

518
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:50,240
we never did anything immoral.

519
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:56,000
Phupha and I never had an affair,

520
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,920
like some people might think.

521
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:05,760
You have to believe me. I swear it.

522
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,080
I believe you.

523
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:46,360
You and Dad
wouldn't have done something like that.

524
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:50,680
Thank you, dear.

525
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:09,640
"Soft Heart"

526
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:13,560
is like a keepsake that Aunt Wilai
left for the man she loved.

527
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:16,160
When you sing this song,

528
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:20,080
you have to convey that feeling.

529
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:22,600
Yes.

530
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:27,840
I'll give it my best.

531
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:35,040
I hope you

532
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,800
succeed

533
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,240
in your singing career, dear.

534
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:51,200
Thank you, Aunt Wilai.

535
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:57,880
But I'm not sure what Boss Nok will think.

536
00:37:58,640 --> 00:38:01,120
I sent him the song a week ago,

537
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:02,920
and it's been quiet.

538
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:05,520
No messages, no reply.

539
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,360
I don't even know if he likes it.

540
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:17,440
Even if he doesn't like it, it's okay.

541
00:38:19,240 --> 00:38:22,000
I'll use my savings from my salary

542
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:23,720
to invest in my music

543
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:27,320
and sing on my own channel.

544
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:34,320
BOSS NOK

545
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,800
Boss Nok is calling!

546
00:38:39,640 --> 00:38:40,720
Hello.

547
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:44,080
-How's it going?
-Hello.

548
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:46,040
Sorry, Teacher.

549
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:49,040
I've been so busy with work lately,

550
00:38:49,120 --> 00:38:51,400
but I just listened

551
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:53,920
to your song, "Soft Heart".

552
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,040
Just a moment.

553
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:57,760
I will put it on speaker,
so Puna can hear it too.

554
00:39:01,720 --> 00:39:04,320
Oh, she's with you too?

555
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:07,400
<i>Hey, Puna.</i>

556
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:10,000
I've just listened to "Soft Heart".

557
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:11,880
And I loved it.

558
00:39:13,160 --> 00:39:14,640
I want to use this song

559
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,960
as your debut single, Puna.

560
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:20,680
<i>Are you free tomorrow?</i>

561
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:24,240
I got the recording studio booked for you.

562
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:28,040
Okay? Come and record it tomorrow.

563
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:33,440
This song will be your debut.

564
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,800
Really, Boss Nok?

565
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:40,040
I heard that right, didn't I?

566
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:41,760
You heard it right.

567
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:44,360
I've decided

568
00:39:44,880 --> 00:39:49,320
to use "Soft Heart" as your debut single.

569
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:51,920
<i>And I promise</i>

570
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:55,760
this song will be a huge hit!

571
00:39:58,160 --> 00:39:59,480
What about the music arrangement?

572
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:01,200
<i>Don't worry.</i>

573
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:03,800
I'm quick on this.

574
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:07,000
I had Ah work on the arrangement
last week.

575
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:09,720
<i>He just sent me the demo.</i>

576
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,960
<i>I tweaked it a little.</i>

577
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:15,680
It'll be ready tomorrow, for sure.

578
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:20,840
Thank you so much, Boss Nok.
Thank you so much!

579
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:24,040
Okay, see you tomorrow.

580
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:25,040
Yes.

581
00:40:31,040 --> 00:40:33,280
Teacher! Aunt Wilai!

582
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:35,480
My dream is coming true!

583
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:37,560
I'm going to be a singer!

584
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:40,680
Yay!

585
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:46,600
Hey, I have to go.

586
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:47,760
Here it comes again.

587
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,680
What now?

588
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:50,000
Another enemy attack!

589
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:51,560
Another enemy attack?

590
00:40:52,720 --> 00:40:53,840
Never mind him.

591
00:40:57,440 --> 00:40:58,520
I'm so happy for you.

592
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,720
A new star!

593
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:12,440
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

594
00:41:14,680 --> 00:41:20,760
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

595
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:24,960
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

596
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:28,280
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

597
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:32,960
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

598
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:38,600
<i>But now, my heart is starting to weaken</i>

599
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:45,720
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

600
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:50,040
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

601
00:41:50,120 --> 00:41:52,880
<i>Every time I see his face</i>

602
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:58,600
<i>My heart pounds</i>

603
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:03,480
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

604
00:42:03,560 --> 00:42:07,160
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

605
00:42:07,240 --> 00:42:09,160
<i>Sing with all your heart today.</i>

606
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:11,840
<i>Make Boss Nok completely amazed.</i>

607
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:12,800
MAKE BOSS NOK COMPLETELY AMAZED

608
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:14,360
I'll be cheering for you.

609
00:42:15,080 --> 00:42:17,600
<i>Before I knew it</i>

610
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:22,280
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

611
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:28,720
<i>Back then, my heart had never wavered</i>

612
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:35,600
<i>Why does it burn, unable to escape?</i>

613
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:39,400
<i>Like iron softened by fire</i>

614
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:42,680
<i>Before the hammer strikes</i>

615
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:47,840
<i>It bends on its own</i>

616
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:58,200
Teacher, if I'm not mistaken,

617
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,200
isn't this song owned
by Kamnan Pong's label?

618
00:43:00,280 --> 00:43:04,040
I feel like using it
might cause problems later.

619
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:05,320
No.

620
00:43:05,840 --> 00:43:08,680
Onanong never gave this song
to anyone else.

621
00:43:08,760 --> 00:43:11,120
As her legal heir,

622
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:14,760
I'm the sole owner of the copyright

623
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:15,680
under the law.

624
00:43:16,840 --> 00:43:19,920
Good, Teacher. Then let's make

625
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:25,080
a copyright agreement properly
for both sides,

626
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:26,840
just to be safe.

627
00:43:26,920 --> 00:43:27,960
Sure, that's fine.

628
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:30,520
Em, bring the copyright documents
to the room.

629
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:37,920
Alright, Teacher?

630
00:43:39,400 --> 00:43:42,120
Take your time. Em,

631
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:43,760
let him read it first.

632
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:46,520
BAI TONG MUSIC

633
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:56,600
Go ahead and sign the copyright,

634
00:43:56,680 --> 00:43:59,440
so we're both clear and at ease.

635
00:43:59,960 --> 00:44:01,400
Yes, Boss.

636
00:44:02,560 --> 00:44:05,640
If we're debuting this song for Puna,

637
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:08,680
may I ask one favor?

638
00:44:09,720 --> 00:44:10,960
What is it?

639
00:44:11,040 --> 00:44:13,280
Don't tell anyone that I'm Onanong's heir.

640
00:44:13,880 --> 00:44:16,760
This has to stay completely secret.
Can you do that?

641
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:19,120
Sure, Teacher.

642
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:21,160
Just sign it.

643
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:41,160
Congratulations.

644
00:44:41,240 --> 00:44:42,200
Thank you.

645
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:48,000
"SOFT HEART", BY PUNA THARARIN

646
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:50,480
<i>Back then, my heart was strong…</i>

647
00:44:50,560 --> 00:44:52,440
Whose voice is that?
Who's singing this song?

648
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:55,320
<i>As tough as a bar of steel…</i>

649
00:44:55,400 --> 00:44:58,320
Exactly. Ice, who is it?

650
00:44:58,400 --> 00:45:00,720
It's amazing, such a clear voice.

651
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:03,120
A new singer?

652
00:45:04,040 --> 00:45:06,680
That's Puna! Don't you remember?

653
00:45:06,760 --> 00:45:08,240
Puna's voice?!

654
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:13,560
Bai Tong Music is promoting her new song.

655
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:16,080
Look, the views are skyrocketing!

656
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:17,440
That's right.

657
00:45:17,520 --> 00:45:19,160
You're right.

658
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:21,400
Let me see!

659
00:45:22,880 --> 00:45:24,920
"SOFT HEART", BY PUNA THARARIN

660
00:45:27,120 --> 00:45:28,440
She's officially a singer.

661
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:32,520
I'm sure she's going to be famous.

662
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:36,000
Yeah! The song is really good.
This is exactly it!

663
00:45:48,760 --> 00:45:53,760
<i>I'd already fallen for him…</i>

664
00:45:53,840 --> 00:45:56,880
Boon! Hey, Boon!

665
00:45:58,120 --> 00:45:59,320
Yes, Kamnan?

666
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:01,520
Who played this song?

667
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:03,800
The workers played it.

668
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:08,000
Impossible.

669
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:10,840
Whose voice is that?

670
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:14,440
It's the new singer named Puna.

671
00:46:15,680 --> 00:46:16,800
Which Puna?

672
00:46:16,880 --> 00:46:18,000
Kamnan!

673
00:46:27,520 --> 00:46:30,040
It's Puna, the one

674
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:33,240
who won the singing contest
with Darathong Music.

675
00:46:38,960 --> 00:46:40,400
I've brought
the company budget for review.

676
00:46:41,160 --> 00:46:42,720
I'll sign it when I have time.

677
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:45,920
Hey.

678
00:46:46,560 --> 00:46:49,760
I just heard the song by that singer Puna.

679
00:46:50,280 --> 00:46:51,680
It really works!

680
00:46:52,320 --> 00:46:54,680
This year, Darathong Music
is going to make a profit for sure.

681
00:46:55,320 --> 00:46:59,280
She's moved to Boss Nok's label now.

682
00:46:59,360 --> 00:47:00,480
What?

683
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:03,040
She won our singing contest!

684
00:47:04,480 --> 00:47:08,280
How could you give her to someone else?
We built her up ourselves!

685
00:47:08,360 --> 00:47:09,280
How could you give her away?

686
00:47:10,320 --> 00:47:13,480
Well, Boss Nok asked for her,

687
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:14,640
so I let her go.

688
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:17,560
How could this happen?
And the budget I approved for Puna,

689
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:18,760
does it still exist?

690
00:47:21,400 --> 00:47:26,720
I've already moved it
to promote Maria and Sonrak's album.

691
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:28,160
Are you crazy?

692
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:31,720
Even though I gave you full control
over Darathong Music,

693
00:47:31,800 --> 00:47:35,240
I'm still the investor!
You should show some respect.

694
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:39,200
I'm really sorry, Kamnan.

695
00:47:40,240 --> 00:47:41,880
I've been so busy.

696
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:44,600
I never meant to hide anything from you.

697
00:47:44,680 --> 00:47:47,200
I just reported it late.

698
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:50,400
Late? Do you know
she won our singing contest?

699
00:47:50,480 --> 00:47:53,880
You just gave her to someone else
and let them snatch the opportunity.

700
00:47:53,960 --> 00:47:55,560
I think that's not right!

701
00:47:55,640 --> 00:47:58,120
We've built her up for so long,
and now you give her away?

702
00:47:59,600 --> 00:48:01,200
Kamnan.

703
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:03,240
Please don't worry.

704
00:48:03,320 --> 00:48:06,320
Even though she is with Boss Nok now,

705
00:48:06,400 --> 00:48:07,920
soon,

706
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:11,560
she'll return to Darathong Music.

707
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:15,280
What are you two going to do about this?

708
00:48:15,880 --> 00:48:17,080
Sonrak.

709
00:48:17,880 --> 00:48:20,680
He'll make this easier to handle.

710
00:48:29,800 --> 00:48:32,400
I heard there's a delivery
scheduled tonight.

711
00:48:33,480 --> 00:48:35,000
But isn't there a concert tonight?

712
00:48:35,520 --> 00:48:36,720
Yes.

713
00:48:36,800 --> 00:48:40,080
They like to use the chaos
as cover to make their deliveries.

714
00:48:40,160 --> 00:48:42,520
NEXT EPISODE

715
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:44,720
Where's Mr. Sonrak's bedroom?

716
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:45,880
Handle her properly.

717
00:48:47,520 --> 00:48:49,560
I'll be leaving now.

718
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:53,080
-Puna.
-Mr. Sonrak, what are you doing?

719
00:48:54,280 --> 00:48:56,840
Don't! Let go of me!

720
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:55,760
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
